'''Haissem Yousry Fouad A Hassan''' ({{langx|arz|هيثم يسري فؤاد حسن}}; born 8 February 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Spanish football updater|Oviedo}} club [[Real Oviedo]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].

== Club career ==
Hassan signed his first professional contract with [[LB Châteauroux|Châteauroux]] on 1 June 2018 at the age of 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.footmercato.net/ligue2/info-fm-a-la-decouverte-de-haissem-hassan-16-ans-et-deja-professionnel-a-chateauroux_230535|title=Info FM : à la découverte de Haissem Hassan, 16 ans et déjà professionnel à Châteauroux|publisher=footmercato.net - Alexis Pereira|date=July 2018}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Châteauroux in a 0–0 [[Ligue 2]] tie with [[Paris FC]] on 19 October 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=FEUILLE DE MATCH PARIS FC - CHÂTEAUROUX|url=https://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuille_match/85098|publisher=lfp.fr|year=2018}}</ref>

On 2 October 2020, Hassan signed a four-year contract with [[Villarreal CF]], being initially assigned to [[Villarreal CF B|the reserves]] in [[Segunda División B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/news/item/28669-villarreal-b-sign-talented-youngster-haissem-hassan|title=Villarreal B sign talented youngster Haissem Hassan|publisher=Villarreal CF|date=2 October 2020|accessdate=9 August 2021}}</ref> The following 9 August, he moved to [[Segunda División]] side [[CD Mirandés]] on a one-year loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdmirandes.com/noticia/haissem-hassan-nuevo-fichaje-del-c-d-mirandes-cedido-por-el-villarreal-cf|title=Haissem Hassan, nuevo fichaje del C.D. Mirandés cedido por el Villarreal CF|trans-title=Haissem Hassan, new signing of C.D. Mirandés on loan from Villarreal CF|publisher=CD Mirandés|language=es|date=9 August 2021|accessdate=9 August 2021}}</ref>

On 1 August 2023, Hassan renewed his contract with the ''Yellow Submarine'' until 2025, and was loaned to [[Sporting de Gijón]] in the second division for [[2023–24 Segunda División|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://villarrealcf.es/haissem-renueva-y-se-va-cedido-al-sporting/|title=Haissem renueva y se va cedido al Sporting|trans-title=Haissem renews and moves out on loan to Sporting|publisher=Villarreal CF|language=es|date=1 August 2023|accessdate=1 August 2023}}</ref> On 11 August 2024, he moved to [[Real Oviedo]], also in the second division, on a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Haissem Hassan, nuevo futbolista del Real Oviedo |trans-title=Haissem Hassan, new Real Oviedo footballer|url=https://www.realoviedo.es/noticias/haissem-hassan-nuevo-futbolista-del-real-oviedo |access-date=11 August 2024 |website=Real Oviedo |language=es}}</ref>

== International career ==
Hassan was born in [[Paris]], France to an [[Egyptian diaspora|Egyptian]] father and [[Tunisians in France|Tunisian]] mother.<ref>{{cite news|title=Berrichonne : Haïssem Hassan, le rêve éveillé|url=https://www.lanouvellerepublique.fr/chateauroux/haissem-hassan-le-reve-eveille|publisher=lanouvellerepublique.fr}}</ref> He was a youth international for France.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maligue2.fr/2018/09/27/haissem-hassan-chateauroux-offre-la-victoire-a-lequipe-de-france-u17/|title=Haissem Hassan (Châteauroux) offre la victoire à l'équipe de France U17 - MaLigue2|date=27 September 2018|publisher=}}</ref>
On March 15, 2026, Hassan agreed to join the [[Egypt national football team]] ahead of the March International Window and to get a chance to play at the [[FIFA World Cup 2026]].

